david lumley's home page welcome to david lumley's home page 2 d seismology lets us image simple geologic structure and faults 3 d seismology allows us to see more intricate features such as buried river channel meanders and complex deformation around salt intrusions but with 4 d seismology i can show you fluid flowing in the earth you can see before and after views at a steam injection site in both cross sectional profile and depth slice map view please read my award winning papers on 4 d seismic monitoring of fluid flow or a brief description of my research interests for further details awards and honors research interests personal information papers to download research movies and pix stanford exploration project home page email david sep stanford edu last updated
